Why Lambdas?

* Enables functional programming
* Readable and concise code
* Easier to use APIand libraries
* Enables support for parallel processing (parallel stream) 


greetingFunction = () -> System.out.println("Hello World");


greet(greetingFunction);

or

**Can pass lambda as inline parameters too
greet(() -> System.out.println("Hello World"));

multiplier = (int arg) -> {
		return arg * 2;
};
		|
		|
multiplier = (int arg) -> arg * 2;
(if only one line you can skip the return word. it is actually invalid. -> actually specifies return)

addFunction = (int a, int b) -> a + b;

safeDivideFunction = (int a, int b) -> {
   			if(b==0) 
   				return 0;
   			return a / b;
   };
   
 stringLengthCountFunction = (String s) -> s.length();
 